ww.tata.com/company/profile/Tata-Consultancy-Services |title=Tata Consultancy Services |publisher=Tata Group |accessdate=6 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Service lines===\nTCS' services are currently organised into the following service lines (percentage of total TCS revenues in the 2012-13 financial year generated by each respective service line is shown in parentheses):\n*Application development and maintenance (43.80%) value;\n*Asset leverage [[solution]]s{{clarify|date=July 2018}} (2.70%);\n*[[Assurance services]] (7.70%);\n*[[Business process outsourcing]] (12.50%);\n*Consulting (2.00%);\n*Engineering and Industrial services (4.60%);\n*Enterprise solution (15.21%); and\n*IT infrastructure services (11.50%).<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" />\n*Cognitive Business Operations<ref>{{cite web |title=Cognitive Business Operations for a Digital World |url=https://www.tcs.com/cognitive-business-operations |website=www.tcs.com |language=en}}</ref>\n*Cloud Infrastructure<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tcs.com/cloud-infrastructure|title=IT Infrastructure Consulting Services and Solutions {{!}} TCS|website=www.tcs.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n*Automation and AI<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tcs.com/automation-and-ai|title=Automation and Artificial Intelligence Services {{!}} TCS|website=www.tcs.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==Operations==\nTata Consultancy Services has 285 offices across 46 countries and 147 delivery centres in 21 countries.<ref name=\"TCS Investor FAQs\" /> At the same date TCS had a total of 58 subsidiary companies.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" />\n\n===Locations===\nTCS has operations in the following locations:\n\n'''India''':\n[[Ahmedabad]], [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]], [[Baroda]],  [[Coimbatore]],  [[Delhi]], [[Gandhinagar]], [[Goa]], [[Gurgaon|Gurugram]], [[Guwahati]], [[Hyderabad]], [[Bhopal]], [[Indore]], [[Jamshedpur]], [[Kochi]], [[Kolkata]], [[Lucknow]], [[Mumbai]], [[Nagpur]], [[Noida]], [[Nashik]], [[Patna]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/union-it-minister-ravi-shankar-prasad-flags-off-new-tcs-centre-in-patna-2231509.html|title=Union IT Minister Ravi Shankar Prasad Opens New TCS Centre in Patna|website=News18|access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/minister-opens-new-tcs-centre/articleshow/70208922.cms|title=Ravi Shankar Prasad opens new TCS centre in Patna {{!}} Patna News - Times of India|last=14 Jul|first=TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=5 September 2019|last3=Ist|first3=9:54}}</ref> [[Pune]], [[Trivandrum]], and [[Varanasi]]\n\n'''Asia (excluding India)''':\n[[Bahrain]], [[China]], [[Israel]], [[UAE]], [[Hong Kong]], [[Indonesia]], [[Japan]], [[Malaysia]], [[Philippines]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Singapore]], [[South Korea]], [[Taiwan]], [[Thailand]], and [[Qatar]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcs.com/worldwide/asia/locations/philippines/Pages/default.aspx |title=TCS Worldwide: Philippines |publisher=Tcs.com |date= |accessdate=13 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinaeconomicreview.com/node/48202|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212811/http://www.chinaeconomicreview.com/node/48202|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 January 2014|title=China Joint Venture with Tata Consultancy Services|work=China Economic Review|date=18 September 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcs.com/worldwide/middle_east_africa/locations/uae/Pages/default.aspx |title=TCS Worldwide: United Arab Emirates (UAE) |publisher=Tcs.com |date= |accessdate=13 November 2011}}</ref>\n\n'''Oceania''':\n[[Australia]]\n\n'''Africa''':\n[[South Africa]], [[Morocco]] (closed)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.expressindia.com/news/fullstory.php?newsid=78005|title=TCS plans Morocco foray with 500-strong unit |publisher=Express Online|date= 12 October 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/tcs-closing-down-morocco-