2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> TCS BPS has more than 45,000 employees which serve over 225 million customers across 11 countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/tcs-named-leader-life-science-143000155.html |title=TCS Named as a Leader in Life Science Drug Safety Services by Leading Industry Research Firm |publisher=Yahoo! Finance |date=28 February 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927213246/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/tcs-named-leader-life-science-143000155.html |archive-date=27 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> The rate of attrition in BPS division during the financial year 2012-13 was 19.5%.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sites.tcs.com/investorsdocs/TCS_Data_Sheet.xlsx |title=Consolidated Historical Financials |publisher=TCS |accessdate=3 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927181406/http://sites.tcs.com/investorsdocs/TCS_Data_Sheet.xlsx |archive-date=27 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, TCS won a $35 million contract from [[Eli Lilly and Company]] for providing [[data management]], [[biostatistics]] and medical writing services.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2006-11-13/news/27444972_1_clinical-trial-tcs-tata-consultancy-services|title=TCS wins $35 mn Eli Lilly contract|work=timesofindia-economictimes|accessdate=2 July 2015|date=13 November 2006|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703111225/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2006-11-13/news/27444972_1_clinical-trial-tcs-tata-consultancy-services|archive-date=3 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oneindia.com/2006/11/15/tcs-with-us-based-eli-lilly-for-advance-clinical-research-1163595890.html|title=TCS with US-based Eli Lilly for advance clinical research|work=www.oneindia.com|accessdate=2 July 2015|date=15 November 2006|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703170856/http://www.oneindia.com/2006/11/15/tcs-with-us-based-eli-lilly-for-advance-clinical-research-1163595890.html|archive-date=3 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2007, it won a major multi-year deal from Swiss [[pharmaceutical]] major [[Hoffmann-La Roche]] to provide data management, [[biostatistics]], clinical programming and [[drug safety]] support to [[Hoffmann-La Roche]]'s global pharmaceutical development efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outsourcing-pharma.com/Commercial-Services/Tata-bags-major-BPO-deal-with-Roche|title=Tata bags major BPO deal with Roche|work=Outsourcing-Pharma.com|accessdate=2 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150616232239/http://www.outsourcing-pharma.com/Commercial-Services/Tata-bags-major-BPO-deal-with-Roche|archive-date=16 June 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-business/tcs-to-support-roches-initiative/article1905634.ece|title=TCS to support Roche's initiative|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2 July 2015|location=Chennai, India|date=5 September 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2007-09-05/news/28468976_1_j-rajagopal-tcs-roche|title=TCS in multi-million dollar deal with Swiss firm|work=timesofindia-economictimes|accessdate=2 July 2015|date=5 September 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703110133/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2007-09-05/news/28468976_1_j-rajagopal-tcs-roche|archive-date=3 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe firm has also opened a business process outsourcing facility in the Philippines.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/articles/88322/20101203/tata-consultancy-services-bpo-shop-in-manila-philippines.htm |title=India's TCS opens BPO shop in Manila, Philippines&nbsp;\u2013 Jobs & Hire |publisher=Ibtimes.com |date=3 December 2010 |accessdate=13 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208060234/http://www.ibtimes.com/articles/88322/20101203/tata-consultancy-services-bpo-shop-in-manila-philippines.htm |archive-date=8 December 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Tata Research Development and Design Centre===\n{{main|Tata Research Development and Design Centre}}\n\nTCS established the first software research centre in [[India]], the '''Tata Research Development and Design Centre''', in [[Pune]], [[India]] in 1981. TRDDC undertakes research in [[Software engineering]], [[Process engineering]] and systems research. Researchers at TRDDC also developed MasterCraft (now a suite of digitization and optimization tools),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcs.com/offerings/mastercraft/Pages/default.aspx|title=TCS Mastercraft Suite of Products|publisher=Tata Consultancy Services|date=1 October 2012|access-date=3 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921232104/http://www.tcs.com/offerings/mastercraft/Pages/default.aspx|archive-date=21 September 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> a [[Model-driven engineering|Model Driven Development]] software that can automatically create code based on a model of a software, and rewrite the code based on the user's needs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iht.com/articles/2005/05/26/business/tata.php|title=When Outsourcing Loses Human Element|publisher=International Herald Tribune|date=27 May 2005|access-date=17 February 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060211010821/http://www.iht.com/articles/2005/05/26/business/tata.php|archive-date=11 February 2006|url-status=live}}</ref> Research at TRDDC has also resulted in the development of Sujal, a low-cost water purifier that can be manufactured using locally available resources. TCS deployed thousands of these filters in the [[Indian Ocean tsunami]] disaster of 2004 as part of its relief activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieee.org/portal/cms_docs_iportals/iportals/aboutus/annualreport/2005/IEEE-AR05-Section1.pdf|title=Improving Our World&nbsp;\u2013 IEEE Annual Report(page 4)|publisher=IEEE|year=2005|access-date=17 February 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090304083137/http://www.ieee.org/portal/cms_docs_iportals/iportals/aboutus/annualreport/2005/IEEE-AR05-Section1.pdf|archive-date=4 March 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> This product has been marketed in [[India]] as [[Tata swach]], a low cost water purifier.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/40000/tata-launches-swach-water-filters.html |title=Tata launches 'Swach' water filters |publisher=Deccanherald. |date=7 December 2009 |accessdate=12 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100302164751/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/40000/tata-launches-swach-water-filters.html |archive-date=2 March 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Innovation Labs===\nIn 2007, TCS launched its co-innovation network, a network of innovation labs, start up alliances, university research departments, and venture capitalists.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/tcs-launches-its-coinnovation-network/191184/ |title=TCS launches its Co-Innovation Network |publisher=Financialexpress.com |date=18 January 2007 |accessdate=16 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615085037/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/tcs-launches-its-coinnovation-network/191184 |archive-date=15 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/network/Pages/default.aspx |title=The TCS Co-Innovation Network |publisher=TCS |accessdate=6 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130920024942/http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/network/Pages/default.aspx |archive-date=20 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition, TCS has 19 innovation labs based in three countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/tcs_labs/Pages/default.aspx |title=Innovation Labs |publisher=TCS |date= |accessdate=16 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100711081924/http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/tcs_labs/Pages/default.aspx |archive-date=11 July 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> TCS' partners include [[Collabnet]], [[William T. Coleman III|Cassatt]], academic institutions such as [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IITs]], [[Stanford]], [[MIT]], [[Carnegie Mellon]] and venture capitalists like [[Sequoia Capital|Sequoia]] and [[Kleiner Perkins]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/network/Pages/default.aspx |title=Co-Innovation Network |publisher=TCS |date= |accessdate=26 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100719075811/http://www.tcs.com/about/tcs_difference/innovation/network/Pages/default.aspx |archive-date=19 July 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Employees==\nTCS is one of the biggest and the largest [[private sector]] employers in [[India]],<ref name=\"TCS\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-17/software-services/38614630_1_march-31-net-profit-new-growth-engines|title=TCS Q4 net profit jumps 22% to Rs 3,597 crore|publisher=Times of India|date=17 April 2013|accessdate=3 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105115606/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-17/software-services/38614630_1_march-31-net-profit-new-growth-engines|archive-date=5 November 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> and the fourth-largest employer among listed [[List of companies of India|Indian companies]] (after [[Indian Railways]], [[Indian Army]] and [[India Post]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/slideshows/nation-world/indias-eight-biggest-employers/slideshow/47861071.cms|title=India's eight biggest employers|website=The Economic Times|access-date=27 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180910014858/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/slideshows/nation-world/indias-eight-biggest-employers/slideshow/47861071.cms|archive-date=10 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> TCS had a total of 4,46,675 employees as of 31 December 2019, of which 36.2% were women.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" /><ref>{{Cite news| url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/top-five-takeaways-what-powered-tcs-to-beat-street-estimates-on-q3-earnings/articleshow/56498799.cms| title=Top five takeaways: What powered TCS to beat Street estimates on Q3 earnings| newspaper=The Economic Times| date=12 January 2017| last1=Anand| first1=Kshitij| access-date=12 January 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112151454/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/top-five-takeaways-what-powered-tcs-to-beat-street-estimates-on-q3-earnings/articleshow/56498799.cms| archive-date=12 January 2017| url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/business/corporate-business/can-tcs-grow-to-500000-employees-or-will-linear-staff-growth-start-impacting-results-1968129.html|title=Can TCS grow to 5,00,000 employees? Or will linear staff growth start impacting results? - Firstpost|website=www.firstpost.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/bkMCAhvRg2xJvLqsLQh88I/TCS-behind-only-IBM-in-employee-strength.html|title=TCS behind only IBM in employee strength|first=Arundhati Ramanthan & Anirban|last=Sen|date=31 March 2013|publisher=|access-date=12 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113170639/http://www.livemint.com/Companies/bkMCAhvRg2xJvLqsLQh88I/TCS-behind-only-IBM-in-employee-strength.html|archive-date=13 January 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The number of non-[[Indian people|Indian]] nationals was 21,282 as on 31 March 2013 (7.7%).<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/tcs-non-indian-employee-number-crosses-21-000-113060700770_1.html |title=TCS non-Indian employee number crosses 21,000 |newspaper=Business Standard |date=7 June 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref>  The employee costs for the FY 2012-13 were US$4.38 billion, which was approx. 38% of the total revenue of the company for that period.<ref name=\"IFRS Annual Report 2012-13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/investors/Documents/Financial%20Statements/TCS_IFRS_Q4_13_USD.PDF |title=Annual Report 2012-13 US GAAP/IFRS |publisher=TCS |date=17 April 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> In the fiscal year 2012-13, TCS recruited a total of 69,728 new staff, of whom 59,276 were based in [[India]] and 10,452 were based in the rest of the world.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" /> In the same period, the rate of attrition was 10.6%.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" /> The average age of a TCS employee is 28 years.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" />  The employee utilisation rate, excluding trainees, for the FY 2012-13 was 82%.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" />\nTCS was the fifth-largest United States visa recipient in 2008 (after [[Infosys]], [[Cognizant Technology Solutions|CTS]], [[Wipro]] and [[Mahindra Satyam]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qYS7C0urmOo |title=Top 8 IT Companies in India|publisher=Yadnya Investment Academy |date= December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.businessweek.com/stories/2009-02-24/indian-firms-microsoft-top-h-1b-listbusinessweek-business-news-stock-market-and-financial-advice |title=Indian Firms, Microsoft Top H-1B List |work=News |publisher=Businessweek |date= 24 February 2009|accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eweek.com/c/a/IT-Management/Indian-Outsourcing-Firms-Top-H1B-Visa-Grants/ |title=Indian Outsourcing Companies Top H-1B Visa List |publisher=eWeek.com |date=2 March 2009 |accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> In 2012, the [[Tata Group]] companies, including TCS, were the second largest recipient of H-1B visas.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/international/top-10-h1b-visa-recipients-outsource-american-jobs-overseas-report/article4434544.ece |title=Top 10 H1B visa recipients outsource American jobs overseas: Report |newspaper=The Hindu |date=20 February 2013 |accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9236732/The_data_shows_Top_H_1B_users_are_offshore_outsourcers?pageNumber=1 |title=The data shows: Top H-1B users are offshore outsourcers |publisher=ComputerWorld |date=14 February 2013 |accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> As of Jan 2020, TCS has over 4,00,000+ employees. It is world's third largest IT employer behind IBM and HP.\n\n[[S Ramadorai|Subramaniam Ramadorai]], former CEO of TCS, has written an autobiographical book about his experiences in the company called ''The TCS Story...and Beyond''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/beyond-business/tcs-the-complete-story-111092100102_1.html |title=TCS: the complete story |newspaper=Business Standard |date=21 September 2011 |accessdate=6 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Sponsorships==\nTCS is the title sponsor for [[Amsterdam Marathon]], [[Mumbai Marathon]] and [[New York City Marathon]]<ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/tcs-title-sponsor-for-new-york-road-runners-113100300366_1.html TCS title sponsor for New York Road Runners]. Business Standard (3 October 2013) Retrieved on 2013-12-06.</ref> and one of the sponsors of [[City2Surf (Sydney)|City2Surf]], Australian Running Festival, [[Berlin Marathon]], [[Chicago Marathon]], and [[Boston Marathon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/about/corp_facts/sponsorships/Pages/default.aspx |title=About TCS \u2013 Corporate Facts \u2013 Sponsorships |publisher=TCS |date= |accessdate=6 September 2013}}</ref> In [[India]], it is the title sponsor of [[World 10K Bangalore|World 10K]] held in Bangalore every year.<ref>{{cite news|title=10 Things you must know about TCS World 10K Marathon 2015|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2015/05/10-things-you-must-know-about-tcs-world-10k-marathon-2015/|accessdate=16 May 2015|publisher=news.biharprabha.com|date=16 May 2015}}</ref> TCS is a sponsor of [[Indian Premier League]] team [[Rajasthan Royals]] since 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/archive/|title=Archive News|website=The Hindu}}</ref> In addition, TCS provides [[Rajasthan Royals]] with technology to help in analysis of player performance, simulation and use of [[RFID]] tags for tracking the players\u2019 fitness levels and for security purposes in the stadiums.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-info-tech/article1048817.ece/|title=TCS is Rajasthan Royals' tech partner|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rajasthanroyals.com/news20090407.aspx/|title=Tata Consultancy Services enters the Indian Premier League|publisher=|access-date=6 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130501172353/http://www.rajasthanroyals.com/news20090407.aspx/|archive-date=1 May 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> TCS sponsors an annual IT quiz for high school students called ''[[TCS IT Wiz]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcsitwiz.com|title=TCS IT Wiz - India's biggest inter-school IT Quiz|website=www.tcsitwiz.com}}</ref> The TCS IT Wiz is the largest quiz in [[India]], attracting students who are studying between class 8 and class 12. This quiz is hosted by [[Giri Balasubramanium]].\n\n==Controversies==\n===Class action lawsuit===\nOn 14 February 2006, U.S. law firm [[Lieff Cabraser Heimann & Bernstein, LLP]] filed a nationwide class-action lawsuit against [[Tata Group|Tata]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lieffcabraser.com/Case-Center/Tata-Workers-in-America-Wages-Class-Action-Lawsuit.shtml|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131030054357/http://www.lieffcabraser.com/Case-Center/Tata-Workers-in-America-Wages-Class-Action-Lawsuit.shtml|url-status=dead|archive-date=30 October 2013|title=Tata Workers in America Wages Class Action Lawsuit|work=Lieff Cabraser Heimann & Bernstein, LLP|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref> In July 2013, judge [[Claudia Wilken]] of the [[U.S. District Court, Northern District of California]] in [[Oakland, California|Oakland]], California, granted final approval to the settlement of the lawsuit on behalf of all non-U.S. citizens employed by TCS within the state of California from 14 February 2002 to 30 June 2005. The workers claimed that they were forced to sign over their federal and state tax refunds to their employer, as well as stating their Indian salaries were wrongfully deducted from their U.S. pay.<ref>{{cite news| url= http://news.in.msn.com/tcs-faces-class-action-lawsuit-in-us| title=TCS faces class-action lawsuit in US| date=4 April 2012 | accessdate= 20 February 2013| work=MSN News| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130507092439/http://news.in.msn.com/tcs-faces-class-action-lawsuit-in-us| archive-date=7 May 2013}}</ref> On 22 February 2013, the company entered into an agreement to settle for a sum of {{INR}}16,163 [[lakh]]s ($29.75 million), this class-action suit filed in a United States Court relating to payment to employees on deputation.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" />\n\nA US grand jury has slapped two companies of [[India]]'s [[Tata Group]] - Tata Consultancy Services and Tata America International Corp - with a US$940 million fine in a trade secret lawsuit filed against them. Epic Systems had accused TCS and Tata America International Corp, in a lawsuit filed in October 2014 in US District Court in Madison which was amended in January and December 2015, of \"brazenly stealing the trade secrets, confidential information, documents and data\" belonging to Epic.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/us-jury-slaps-940-million-fine-on-tcs-tata-america-international-corp-in-trade-secret-case/articleshow/51853894.cms|title=US jury slaps $940 million fine on TCS, Tata America International Corp in trade secret case|date=16 April 2016|publisher=|newspaper=The Economic Times}}</ref>  This Epic Systems lawsuit against TCS was closed and settled with an undisclosed out of court agreement that was completed in January 2018.\n\nA federal class-action lawsuit accusing Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. of bias against U.S.-born workers could be heard by the Court during a Jury Trial starting in November 2018.  The US Federal Court Case in Northern District of California (Buchanan v. Tata Consultancy Servs., Ltd., 4:15-cv-01696) is one of seven across the USA asserting that several large off-shore and national IT staffing companies with operations in the US, prefer foreign workers from [[Indian subcontinent|South Asia]] over qualified Americans. All of the companies being sued are heavy users of H-1B guestworker visas, which go to skilled professionals in \u201cspecialty occupations.\u201d  The US Federal District Court Case 15-cv-01696-YGR seeks to consolidate these lawsuits against TCS and several other IT staffing companies into a class action trial and is allowed by the Federal District Court to proceed (but not yet certified) with a possible November 2018 Jury Trial.\n\n=== Accusations of discrimination ===\nIn May 2013, the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] (CBC), in its extensive coverage of the hiring of temporary foreign workers in Canada and the unemployment issues faced by Canadians, reported that TCS rarely hires skilled experienced Canadians at the [[Toronto]] offices while advertising open positions in Canada. TCS responded that the company hired more than 125 Canadian workers in 2013 who make less than 1.2% of the 10,452 workers the company has outside of India.<ref name=\"AnnualReport1213\" /><ref>{{cite news |author= |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2013/05/17/bc-foreignworkers.html |title=Canadian on EI shut out amid foreign worker influx \u2013 British Columbia \u2013 CBC News |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=20 May 2013 |accessdate=10 June 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130520191930/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2013/05/17/bc-foreignworkers.html |archive-date=20 May 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, a [[class-action|class-action lawsuit]] against TCS was filed in a San Francisco federal court by a U.S. information technology worker and ex-employee, who accused the company of discriminating against American workers by favoring South Asians in hiring and promotion. The lawsuit claimed that [[Indian people|South Asians]] comprise 95% of the company's 14,000-person U.S. workforce and that TCS engaged in discriminatory practices by sourcing most of its workforce through the [[H-1B visa]] program, by focusing its U.S.-based hiring disproportionately on South Asians and by favoring [[Indian people|South Asian]] employees in its [[human resources]] practices. In response, TCS refuted the plaintiff's claims, assuring that it is an equal opportunity employer and bases its employment practices on non-discriminatory reasons. A spokesperson said that in 2014 alone the company had recruited over 2,600 U.S. hires.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Thibodeau|first1=Patrick|title=IT worker's lawsuit accuses Tata of discrimination|url=http://www.computerworld.com/article/2910327/it-workers-lawsuit-accuses-tata-of-discrimination.html|accessdate=16 April 2015|work=ComputerWorld|date=16 April 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416111146/http://www.computerworld.com/article/2910327/it-workers-lawsuit-accuses-tata-of-discrimination.html|archive-date=16 April 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[HCL Technologies|HCL]]\n*[[Zoho Corporation|Zoho]]\n*[[Wipro]]\n*[[Tech Mahindra]]\n*[[List of public corporations by market capitalization]]\n* [[List of IT consulting firms]]\n* [[List of Indian IT companies]]\n* [[List of companies of India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\nhttps://www.tcs.com/tcs-financial-results-q4-fy-2020\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Tata Consultancy Services}}\n* {{Official}}\n* {{finance links\n| name = Tata Consultancy Services Ltd.\n| symbol = TCS.NS\n| hoovers = Tata_Consultancy_Services_Limited.90ce83918a7bfc6c\n}}\n\n{{Tata Group}}\n{{BSE Sensex}}\n{{CNX Nifty companies}}\n{{Major information technology consulting and outsourcing companies}}\n\n[[Category:Tata Consultancy Services| ]]\n[[Category:BSE SENSEX]]\n[[Category:CNX Nifty]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Technology companies established in 1968]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Bombay Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Information technology consulting firms of India]]\n[[Category:International information technology consulting firms]]\n[[Category:MES software]]\n[[Category:Outsourcing companies]]\n[[Category:Software companies of India]]\n[[Category:Information technology companies of Bhubaneswar]]\n[[Category:Information technology companies of India]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Consulting firms established in 1968]]\n[[Category:Software companies based in Mumbai]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian IT company}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = TATA Consultancy Services LTD.\n| logo = TATA Consultancy Services Logo.svg\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{Unbulleted list|{{BSE|532540}}|{{NSE|TCS}}|[[BSE SENSEX|BSE SENSEX Constituent]]|[[CNX Nifty|CNX Nifty Constituent]]}}\n| industry = [[IT service management|IT services]], [[Information technology consulting|IT consulting]]\n| founder = {{Unbulleted list|[[Tata Sons]]|}}\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| key_people = [[Natarajan Chandrasekaran]] <br />{{small|(Chairman)}} <br />[[Rajesh Gopinathan]] <br />{{small|(MD & CEO)}}\n| services = {{hlist |[[Outsourcing]]|[[Consulting]]|[[Managed services]]}}\n| revenue = {{nowrap| {{Increase}} {{USD|22.031 billion|link=yes}} (2020)<ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\" /> }}\n| operating_income = {{Increase}} {{USD|5.3 billion}} (2019)<ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\" />\n| net_income = {{Increase}} {{USD|4.5 billion}} (2019)<ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\" />\n| assets = {{Increase}} {{USD|16.6 billion}} (2019)<ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\" />\n| equity = {{Decrease}} {{USD|13.2 billion}} (2019)<ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\" />\n| num_employees = 448,464 (March 2020)<ref>https://www.tcs.com/content/dam/tcs/investor-relations/financial-statements/2019-20/q2/IND%20AS/Press%20Release%20-%20INR.pdf</ref>\n| parent = [[Tata Sons]]\n| subsid = {{Unbulleted list|[[TCS China]]|[[TRDDC]]}}\n| foundation = {{start date and age|df=yes|1968}}\n| location = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.tcs.com/}}\n| footnotes = <ref name=\"AR1213IFRS\">{{cite web |url= https://www.tcs.com/content/dam/tcs/investor-relations/financial-statements/2018-19/q4/IFRS/Press%20Release%20-%20USD.pdf |title=Press Release - USD |publisher=Tata Consultancy Services |date=12 April 2019 |accessdate=13 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n'''TATA Consultancy Services Limited''' ('''TCS''') is the biggest Indian [[Multinational corporation|multinational]] [[information technology]] (IT) [[service (economics)|service]] and [[Information technology consulting|consulting]] company, and is headquartered in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/companies/tata-consultancy-services/ |title=Tata Consultancy Services |work=Forbes |date=29 August 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/companyProfile?symbol=TCS.NS |title=Tata Consultancy Services Ltd (TCS.NS) |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> It is a subsidiary of [[Tata Group]] and operates in 149 locations across 46 countries.<ref name=\"TCS Investor FAQs\">{{cite web| url = http://www.tcs.com/investors/investor-faq/Pages/default.aspx#q3 | title = TCS Investor FAQs|publisher=TCS|date=June 2014|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nTCS is the largest [[List of companies of India|Indian company]] by [[market capitalization|market capitalisation]].<ref>{{cite news\n| url = http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/TCS-market-value-crosses-Rs-4-lakh-crore-stock-at-all-time-high/articleshow/22230461.cms | title = TCS market value crosses Rs 7 lakh crore \u2013 stock at all-time-high | work = Times of India | date = 2 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://profit.ndtv.com/news/market/article-tcs-market-cap-crosses-rs-4-lakh-crore-reliance-industries-a-distant-no-2-326621 |title=TCS market cap crosses Rs. 4 lakh crore |date=2 September 2013 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> Tata consultancy services is now placed among the most valuable IT services brands worldwide.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/PUF7Vb4EpAu7RKYGmxdE1M/TCS-brand-value-exceeds-5-billion.html | title=TCS brandvalue exceeds 5 billion}}</ref> In 2015, TCS was ranked 64th overall in the ''[[Forbes]]'' World's Most Innovative Companies ranking, making it both the highest-ranked IT services company and the top [[List of companies of India|Indian company]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/companies/tata-consultancy-services/ | work=Forbes | title=Tata Consultancy Services on the Forbes Asia's Fab 50 Companies List}}</ref> It is the world's largest IT services provider.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cio.com/article/3030989/outsourcing/the-top-10-it-outsourcing-service-providers-of-the-year.html|title=The top 10 IT outsourcing service providers of the year \u2013 and the top 10 challengers|first=Stephanie|last=Overby|publisher=|date=15 March 2018|access-date=4 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704213635/https://www.cio.com/article/3030989/outsourcing/the-top-10-it-outsourcing-service-providers-of-the-year.html|archive-date=4 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> As of 2018, it is ranked eleventh on the [[Fortune India 500]] list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fortuneindia.com/fortune-500/company-list/tata-consultancy-services?year=2018|title=Tata Consultancy Services - Fortune 500 List 2018 - Fortune India|website=www.fortuneindia.com|language=en|access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref> In April 2018, TCS became the first Indian IT company to reach $100 billion market capitalisation,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-market-cap-more-than-the-gdp-of-these-countries/articleshow/63894564.cms|title=TCS market-cap more than the GDP of these countries|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424231310/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-market-cap-more-than-the-gdp-of-these-countries/articleshow/63894564.cms|archive-date=24 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and second [[List of companies of India|Indian company]] ever (after [[Reliance Industries]] achieved it in 2007)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-breaches-100-billion-market-in-m-cap-first-indian-it-firm-to-do-so/articleshow/63882361.cms|title=TCS breaches $100 billion market in m-cap; first Indian IT firm to do so|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425031921/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-breaches-100-billion-market-in-m-cap-first-indian-it-firm-to-do-so/articleshow/63882361.cms|archive-date=25 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> after its market capitalisation stood at {{INR}}6,79,332.81 [[crore]] ($102.6 billion) on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-becomes-first-indian-company-to-become-100-billion-company/articleshow/63876020.cms|title=TCS becomes first Indian company to breach $100 billion market capitalisation|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180423231314/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-becomes-first-indian-company-to-become-100-billion-company/articleshow/63876020.cms|archive-date=23 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-is-now-valued-more-than-accenture/articleshow/63888515.cms|title=TCS is now valued more than Accenture|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424135627/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tcs-is-now-valued-more-than-accenture/articleshow/63888515.cms|archive-date=24 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Money/o51TW4N6TuiMuOLKwGOr1H/TCSs-record-100-billion-valuation-is-riding-on-a-wing-and.html|title=TCS's record $100 billion valuation is riding on a wing and a prayer|date=24 April 2018|access-date=24 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180424071928/https://www.livemint.com/Money/o51TW4N6TuiMuOLKwGOr1H/TCSs-record-100-billion-valuation-is-riding-on-a-wing-and.html|archive-date=24 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016\u20132017, Parent company [[Tata Sons]] owned 72.05% of TCS;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/business/ishaat-hussain-appointed-chairman-of-tata-consultancy-services-1310369.html |title=Ishaat Hussain to Replace Cyrus Mistry as Chairman of Tata Consultancy Services |publisher=News18.com |date=10 November 2016 |accessdate=8 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129132552/https://www.news18.com/news/business/ishaat-hussain-appointed-chairman-of-tata-consultancy-services-1310369.html |archive-date=29 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> and more than 70% of Tata Sons' dividends were generated by TCS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/ClQdBjPBMR6VybRSLsCctN/Tata-Sons-may-name-new-chairman-as-early-as-today.html|title=TCS has also accounted for at least 70% of Tata Sons dividends in the past three years, which would have worked in Chandrasekaran's favour |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=8 October 2018 }}</ref> In March 2018, Tata Sons decided to sell stocks of TCS worth $1.25 billion in a bulk deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tata-to-sell-1-25-billion-stake-in-tcs-to-pay-debt/articleshow/63282529.cms?from=mdr|title=Tata to sell its stakes worth $1.25 billion in TCS to pay debt|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=7 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181007223133/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/tata-to-sell-1-25-billion-stake-in-tcs-to-pay-debt/articleshow/63282529.cms?from=mdr|archive-date=7 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n=== 1968\u20132003 ===\nTata Consultancy Services Limited, initially started as \"Tata Computer Systems\" was founded in 1968 by  division of [[Tata Sons|Tata Sons Limited]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcs.com/about/corp_facts/Pages/default.aspx |title=Corporate Facts |publisher=TCS |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> Its early contracts included [[punched card]] services to sister company TISCO (now [[Tata Steel]]), working on an Inter-Branch Reconciliation System for the [[Central Bank of India]],<ref name=\"ICMR\">{{cite web |url= http://www.icmrindia.org/casestudies/catalogue/Business%20Strategy2/Tata%20Consultancy%20Services%20Limited%20The%20Pioneer%20in%20the%20Indian%20IT%20Industry.htm|title=Tata Consultancy Services Limited: The Pioneer in the Indian IT Industry|work=Case Study |publisher=ICMR|date= 1 January 1990|accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> and providing bureau services to [[Unit Trust of India]].\n\nIn 1975, TCS delivered an electronic depository and trading system called SECOM for the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] company {{ill|SIS SegaInterSettle|de}}; it also developed System X for the Canadian Depository System and automated the [[Johannesburg Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/archive.html?siteSect=883&sid=957178&ty=st|title=Indian software keeps Swiss securities safe|publisher=Swissinfo.com|date= 14 January 2002}}</ref> TCS associated with a Swiss partner, TKS Teknosoft, which it later acquired.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.financialexpress.com/news/tcs-acquires-swiss-firm-tksteknosoft/182435/ |title=TCS acquires TKS Teknosoft|work=The Financial Express|date= 11 January 2006}}</ref>\n\nIn 1980, TCS established India's first dedicated software research and development centre, the Tata Research Development and Design Centre (TRDDC) in Pune.<ref>{{Cite journal|last = Kanavi|first = Shivanand|title = Megasoft|journal=Business India| pages=46\u201354|date=7\u201320 June 2004}}</ref> In 1981, it established India's first client-dedicated offshore development centre, set up for clients [[Tandem Computers|Tandem]]. TCS later (1993) partnered with Canada-based software factory Integrity Software Corp, which TCS later acquired.\n\nIn anticipation of the [[Y2K]] bug and the launch of a unified European currency (Euro), Tata Consultancy Services created the factory model for Y2K conversion and developed [[software tools]] which automated the conversion process and enabled third-party developer and client implementation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dqindia.ciol.com/content/top_stories/2004/104122201.asp|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080128103009/http://dqindia.ciol.com/content/top_stories/2004/104122201.asp|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 January 2008|title=IT Man of the Year: Standing Tall|work=Cover Story|publisher=Dataquest India|date=22 December 2004}}</ref> Towards the end of 1999, TCS decided to offer Decision Support System (DSS) in the domestic market under its Corporate Vice President and Transformation Head Subbu Iyer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://expressindia.indianexpress.com/fe/daily/19981209/34355174p.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114184639/http://expressindia.indianexpress.com/fe/daily/19981209/34355174p.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=14 January 2018|title=Financial Express: Tata Consultancy likely to offer decision-support solutions|website=expressindia.indianexpress.com|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2004 to present===\nOn 25 August 2004, TCS became a [[Public company|Publicly Listed Company]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/with-100-billion-m-cap-tcs-is-an-outlier/articleshow/63891810.cms|title=With $100 billion m-cap, TCS is an outlier|newspaper=The Economic Times|date=24 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.hindu.com/2004/06/15/stories/2004061502001000.htm|title=Star Performer Goes Public |work=Editorial |publisher=The Hindu|date= 14 June 2004 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005, TCS became the first India-based IT services company to enter the [[bioinformatics]] market.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.expresscomputeronline.com/20040802/indianews03.shtml |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040816185800/http://www.expresscomputeronline.com/20040802/indianews03.shtml |url-status=dead |archive-date=16 August 2004 |title=TCS launches the country's first bioinformatics product |work=The Indian Express |date=8 February 2004 }}</ref>  In 2006, it designed an [[Enterprise Resource Planning|ERP]] system for the [[Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://egovonline.net/interview/interview-details.asp?interviewid=808|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927011559/http://egovonline.net/interview/interview-details.asp?interviewid=808|url-status=dead|archive-date=27 September 2011|title=ICT helps IRCTC book 3.5 lakh e-Tickets in a day|work=E-GovOnline.net|date=11 July 2011}}</ref> By 2008, its e-business activities were generating over US$500 million in annual revenues.<ref>{{Cite journal|last = Kanavi|first = Shivanand|title = Megasoft|journal=Business India| page=52|date=7\u201320 June 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hindustantimes.com/StoryPage/StoryPage.aspx?sectionName=NLetter&id=c96ab585-b99a-4521-9939-18d8253cf710&MatchID1=4924&TeamID1=4&TeamID2=2&MatchType1=1&SeriesID1=1244&PrimaryID=4924&Headline=Eye+on+future%2c+TCS+in+revamp+mode|title=Eye on future, TCS in revamp mode|work=Hindustan Times|date= 12 February 2008}}</ref>\n\nTCS entered the [[small and medium enterprises]] market for the first time in 2011, with [[cloud computing|cloud]]-based offerings.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.computerweekly.com/Articles/2011/02/15/245449/TCS-targets-SME-market-with-cloud-computing.htm|title=TCS targets SME market with cloud computing|work=Computer Weekly |date= 15 February 2011}}</ref> On the last trading day of 2011, it overtook [[Reliance Industries Limited|RIL]] to achieve the highest market capitalisation of any [[India]]-based company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/tcs-overtakes-ril-as-countrys-most-valued-firm_641999.html |title=TCS overtakes RIL as country's most valued firm&nbsp;\u2013 PTI |publisher=Moneycontrol.com |date=30 December 2011 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> In the 2011/12 fiscal year, TCS achieved annual revenues of over US$10 billion for the first time.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/technology/tcs-beats-10-bn-revenue-mark-in-fy12-112042400081_1.html |title=TCS beats $10-bn revenue mark in FY12 |newspaper=Business Standard |date=24 April 2012 |accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013, TCS was awarded a six-year contract worth over {{INR}}1100 [[crore]] to provide services to the Indian [[Indian Postal Service|Department of Posts]].<ref>[http://www.tcs.com/news_events/press_releases/Pages/Department-Posts-Core-System-Integrator-project-TCS.aspx TCS News & Events: Press Release : Department of Posts Awards Core System Integrator project to TCS]. Tcs.com. Retrieved on 6 December 2013.</ref> In 2013, the firm moved from the 13th position to 10th position in the ''League of top 10 global IT services companies''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/TCS-joins-top-10-global-IT-services-companies-club/articleshow/34067479.cms|title=TCS joins top 10 global IT services companies club|work=The Times of India|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref> and in July 2014, it became the first [[List of companies of India|Indian company]] with over {{INR}}5 [[lakh]] [[crore]] market capitalization.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/TCS-first-Indian-company-to-top-Rs-5-lakh-crore-market-cap/articleshow/38940093.cms| title= TCS first Indian company to top Rs 5 lakh crore market cap| date= 24 July 2014 | publisher= Times Of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.btvin.com/videos/watch/8117/tcs-crosses-rs.5-lk-cr-market-cap| title= TCS Crosses Rs.5 Lk Cr Market Cap| date= 24 July 2014 | publisher= [[Bloomberg TV India]]}}</ref>\n\nIn Jan 2015, TCS ends [[Reliance Industries Limited|RIL]]'s 23-year run as most profitable firm<ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/TCS-ends-RILs-23-year-run-as-most-profitable-firm/articleshow/45947297.cms| title= TCS ends RIL's 23-year run as most profitable firm| date= 20 January 2014 | publisher= Times Of }}</ref>\n\nIn Jan 2017, the company announced a partnership with Aurus, Inc., a payments technology company, to deliver payment [[solution]]s for retailers using TCS OmniStore, a first of its kind unified store commerce platform.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/tcs-tcs-partners-with-aurus-to-enhance-omnichannel-payment-solutions-with-omnistore-117011600323_1.html|title=TCS {{!}} TCS partners with Aurus to enhance Omnichannel payment solutions with OmniStore|last=indiainfoline.com|access-date=17 January 2017}}</ref> In the same year, TCS China was associated as a joint venture with the Chinese government.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/company/tata-consultancy-services-ltd-5400/information/company-history|title=Tata Consultancy Services Ltd.|work=Business Standard India|access-date=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nTCS announced its FY19 Q3 results posting 24 percent year-on-year (YoY) rise in profit at {{INR}}8,105 [[crore]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnbctv18.com/earnings/tcs-posts-net-profit-rs-8105-crore-in-q3-1921841.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=11 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111232657/https://www.cnbctv18.com/earnings/tcs-posts-net-profit-rs-8105-crore-in-q3-1921841.htm |archive-date=11 January 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The stock plunged 2.5 percent intra-day as brokerages cut price target.<ref>https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/stocks/market/tcs-shares-fall-as-q3-margins-disappoint-infosys-drops-ahead-of-results-1929741.htm</ref>\n\nTCS Honoured with Four Stevies\u00ae at the 2019 American Business Awards\u00ae<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-cm/tcs-honored-with-four-stevies-at-the-2ol9-american-business-awards-119052301531_1.html|title=Tata Consultancy Services Ltd.|work=Business Standard India|access-date=23 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Acquisitions===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Name\n! data-sort-type=\"date\"|Acquisition date\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Activities\n! data-sort-type=\"text\"|Country of HQ\n! data-sort-type=\"currency\"|Price\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"|Employees<br />(at acquisition)\n! |Description\n! | Sources\n|-\n| [[CMC Limited]]\n| 2001 October\n| IT Services\n| {{flag|IND}}\n| $33.9 m\n| 3,102\n| Gets Embedded Expertise & good Domestic customer reach.  CMC Amalgamated with TCS on 28 April 2015.[http://www.tcs.com/investors/Pages/TCS-CMC.aspx]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/2001/10/18/stories/06180008.htm |title=TCS outlines vision for CMC|publisher=The Hindu |date=17 October 2001 |accessdate=7 September 2013 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tata.in/company/articles/inside.aspx?artid=uC+qBm8g4A0= |title=TCS acquires CMC |publisher=Tata Group |date=17 October 2001 |accessdate=7 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525145343/http://tata.in/company/articles/inside.aspx?artid=uC+qBm8g4A0= |archive-date=25 May 2013 |url-status=dead }